What Is Defamation?
Defamation occurs when someone makes a false statement about you that causes harm to your reputation. This can take the form of written statements (libel) or spoken statements (slander). Defamation is not just about hurt feelings—false claims can damage your career, your relationships, and your standing in the community.
At J. Haskins Law, we understand the serious consequences of defamation and are here to help you fight back. Whether you’re dealing with traditional defamation or its more modern form—internet defamation—our team will stand by your side to restore your reputation.

